# Changelog-lint ignore list
#
# Each non-comment, non-blank line is a commit SHA (full or prefix) to
# skip when running `generate_changelog.py --check`. The abbreviated
# hash is 12 characters by default; listing at least the first 7 works.
#
# This file is the escape hatch for GitHub squash-merge commits whose
# subjects don't follow conventional commits, where rewriting main
# history would be more disruptive than living with the exception.
#
# Lines starting with '#' are comments. Inline comments after a SHA
# (separated by whitespace) are also ignored.
#
# When possible, PREFER fixing the PR title BEFORE squash-merging
# instead of adding the SHA here. See lesson #32 in
# docs/internal/github-release-playbook.md for background.

# 601f6320b413 — "Docs/harness hardening (#2)"
#   PR #2 was squash-merged with a non-conventional title. The fix
#   ("docs: harness hardening") was not applied before merge, so the
#   commit landed on main with an invalid subject. Rewriting this
#   commit on main is destructive; listing it here keeps the lint green
#   for all downstream PRs until the next tag cut moves the `<tag>..HEAD`
#   window past it.
601f6320b413

